  <!-- STEP 2 -->
  <div class="fio-card fio-soft">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">2) Choose Your View</h2>
    <p class="fio-p">Finviz has multiple “views” depending on what you want to analyze.</p>
    <ul class="fio-list">
      <li><strong>Overview:</strong> market cap, price, volume</li>
      <li><strong>Valuation:</strong> P/E, EPS, growth metrics</li>
      <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> insider + institutional ownership</li>
      <li><strong>Performance:</strong> short/long-term performance</li>
      <li><strong>Technical:</strong> moving averages, RSI, indicators</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="fio-p fio-note fio-muted">
      Use the dropdown menu on the upper right to switch views.
    </p>

    <figure class="wp-block-image">
      <img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXe3NW_R0-j8gtbDRJQMFCX1qNfH4ZTQuZ1wtkcLLp7RhlbrwiRqOIT_mk7A08LjOqB4-Ba-a6PuLYpIU-iWf08EV6fEdbcOq4C65aoytFWKm6lRRua9jODSeiLH4zm5EP_EUJNekA?key=EHal6qEyYjyaJ7OatsBxDXiW" alt="Finviz view selector dropdown" />
    </figure>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 3 -->
  <div class="fio-card">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">3) Apply Filters</h2>
    <p class="fio-p">
      Filters are under the menu and grouped into <strong>Descriptive</strong>, <strong>Fundamental</strong>, and <strong>Technical</strong>.
      Click any dropdown, choose your criteria, and the results refresh automatically.
    </p>

    <ul class="fio-list">
      <li><strong>Descriptive:</strong> sector, industry, country, market cap, price, IPO date</li>
      <li><strong>Fundamental:</strong> P/E, EPS growth, dividend, ROE, debt/equity</li>
      <li><strong>Technical:</strong> moving averages, RSI, patterns</li>
    </ul>

    <figure class="wp-block-image">
      <img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdZwSiVwgWrqFM_PMTbYoJnICXj_C890fb4-7CtllNDBImThrU-pTRuXarY-oP1MnTjANoSxvUrKxJAGW3t-UevdgJIWSt8aPH956UoL5bb7b4rqvqhpqTKhlQhhLzUbuvK4j_JIg?key=EHal6qEyYjyaJ7OatsBxDXiW" alt="Finviz filter bar with descriptive, fundamental, technical categories" />
    </figure>

    <p class="fio-p"><strong>How to set a filter:</strong></p>
    <ol class="fio-list">
      <li>Click the dropdown under a parameter (example: <strong>Price</strong>).</li>
      <li>Select the range you want (example: <strong>Over $10</strong>).</li>
    </ol>

    <figure class="wp-block-image">
      <img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXeX_JxAffeOtix2iFxg3cqCJOpFso4J4-_7XBuwHZpFEqSvx4QziPEufmdgzu2qkfcuehuIwzQr55qNritcU0wM-YswatvTbf9o37CCE5LvYa-hnKtvhTI5sAxCWTVIX4yfHJfu?key=EHal6qEyYjyaJ7OatsBxDXiW" alt="Example of selecting a filter dropdown in Finviz" />
    </figure>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 4 -->
  <div class="fio-card fio-soft">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">4) Refine and Sort</h2>
    <ul class="fio-list">
      <li>Once filters are selected, Finviz refreshes results automatically.</li>
      <li>To sort results, click any column header (Volume, Market Cap, P/E). Click again to reverse the sort.</li>
    </ul>

    <figure class="wp-block-image">
      <img src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcBcESjbL8YOtA0QiNBU5dXHEdonUIH9lH2H8EYYLrIUok5RUVpFM57DNpMtsBCBZs7O_P-pBiCTlf_QaRtpGPpF3ty1FhrbwAIvc_KvntkhEVbHLp1W2tCLGb9tXnykQQlDUSqnA?key=EHal6qEyYjyaJ7OatsBxDXiW" alt="Finviz results table and sortable columns" />
